import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of prices in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
